1051
00:59:44.720 --> 00:59:47.040
And, I won't dwell on this. You can read about it.

1052
00:59:47.400 --> 00:59:51.150
It was work we did some time ago. We just used regional spatial proteomics,

1053
00:59:51.210 --> 00:59:54.730
not even single-cell. And we looked on treatment, and we learned that we could

1054
00:59:54.740 --> 00:59:58.480
predict based on the delta in protein changes, which patients would

1055
00:59:58.520 --> 01:00:02.460
achieve a pCR.We reduced that to a very simple digital pathology

1056
01:00:02.520 --> 01:00:06.200
assay, and we're now validating it in a completed Phase 3 trial with a view that we

1057
01:00:06.240 --> 01:00:09.120
can potentially spare women unnecessary chemo.

1058
01:00:09.140 --> 01:00:12.500
So this was our first hope that even though we only had core biopsies, we could

1059
01:00:12.520 --> 01:00:12.980
learn something.

1060
01:00:13.780 --> 01:00:17.440
And more recently, in work that was just published a few months ago,

1061
01:00:18.400 --> 01:00:22.140
we did something similar but with higher resolution technology in the tonic

1062
01:00:22.180 --> 01:00:25.820
trial. This was looking at anti-PD-1 in metastatic triple-negative breast cancer.

1063
01:00:25.860 --> 01:00:29.280
We had multiple biopsies throughout the treatment course, and we did single-cell

1064
01:00:29.300 --> 01:00:33.100
spatial proteomics. And so I'll just briefly say, this was a pretty remarkable

1065
01:00:33.140 --> 01:00:36.710
longitudinal dataset where not only do we have the primary

1066
01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:40.080
tumors, but we have the baseline pre-treatment with nivo

1067
01:00:41.080 --> 01:00:43.180
and then on nivo. And

1068
01:00:44.380 --> 01:00:46.620
we collected a variety of modalities.

1069
01:00:47.020 --> 01:00:50.720
Of course, we studied the TME, as I mentioned, with 37plex MIBI

1070
01:00:50.900 --> 01:00:54.489
spatial proteomics. We also did RNA sequencing, whole exome sequencing,

1071
01:00:55.040 --> 01:00:58.600
and you can start to imagine that we can compare static features as well

1072
01:00:58.680 --> 01:01:02.380
as dynamic features in the TME and ask, what predicts response to

1073
01:01:02.460 --> 01:01:05.220
nivo, since we know it's only a subset of patients that benefit.

1074
01:01:05.900 --> 01:01:09.600
And I'll cut to the chase and just say one of the key findings observed from this

1075
01:01:09.680 --> 01:01:13.520
is that spatial niches really matter, even in these tiny biopsies.

1076
01:01:13.530 --> 01:01:16.900
So actually here, the diversity at the

1077
01:01:16.980 --> 01:01:20.910
cancer border. We've segmented out the populations of cells, we've

1078
01:01:20.960 --> 01:01:24.530
labeled them, as you can see here. So the cell diversity at

1079
01:01:24.560 --> 01:01:28.540
the neighborhood of the surrounding tumor actually

1080
01:01:28.560 --> 01:01:31.920
predicts response. And you can see this for patient 64, which is highlighted right

1081
01:01:31.980 --> 01:01:35.360
here. So I think this tells us that spatial

1082
01:01:35.380 --> 01:01:38.380
topography tells us quite a bit about who's going to achieve a

1083
01:01:38.420 --> 01:01:42.150
response. And I'll just say furthermore, that actually studying

1084
01:01:42.180 --> 01:01:45.030
tumors throughout disease tells us that different features are predictive at

1085
01:01:45.060 --> 01:01:48.940
different times. So maybe not surprisingly, if you look at the many

1086
01:01:49.460 --> 01:01:53.020
hundreds of features we can compute from these spatial proteomic data, there's a

1087
01:01:53.060 --> 01:01:55.240
lot more that are predictive at the on-nivo time point.

1088
01:01:56.040 --> 01:01:59.450
And we could have a whole debate about which features we need, but

1089
01:02:00.400 --> 01:02:04.140
you might be also surprised to see that in this analysis, the RNA is as

1090
01:02:04.180 --> 01:02:07.800
predictive as the protein in determining response.

1091
01:02:07.880 --> 01:02:11.610
Arguably, mechanistically, we can learn more from the spatial proteomics, but I

1092
01:02:11.660 --> 01:02:14.420
just want to say there's a lot to contemplate if we're going to actually make

1093
01:02:14.460 --> 01:02:15.709
longitudinal measurements of disease.

1094
01:02:17.120 --> 01:02:21.060
So, this leads me to say that that was really a focus on

1095
01:02:21.100 --> 01:02:24.960
understanding how we can measure response to therapy

1096
01:02:25.020 --> 01:02:28.900
through spatial efforts. And over the many years, we've helped

1097
01:02:28.960 --> 01:02:31.000
to delineate new subgroups of breast cancer.

1098
01:02:31.340 --> 01:02:34.840
I want to stress that we've known for a long time there are some 14, 15% of breast

1099
