1100
01:02:38.800 --> 01:02:41.820
receptor positive tumors, we've defined some eight subgroups.

1101
01:02:42.080 --> 01:02:44.780
Four of those have an exceptionally high risk of relapse.

1102
01:02:44.840 --> 01:02:47.940
Their risk is in excess of 55% for two decades.

1103
01:02:47.980 --> 01:02:51.560
You can see these women that are ER positive high risk in orange do as poor as

1104
01:02:51.580 --> 01:02:55.540
women with HER2 positive disease before the routine use of trastuzumab.

1105
01:02:56.040 --> 01:02:57.820
We still don't optimally treat these women.

1106
01:02:57.840 --> 01:03:00.720
They are very, very different than their typical risk counterparts in blue.

1107
01:03:01.360 --> 01:03:04.709
And what's special about them is that they have focal copy number amplifications,

1108
01:03:04.840 --> 01:03:07.680
much like HER2, but at different loci throughout the genome.

1109
01:03:07.700 --> 01:03:10.080
17q23 is integrative cluster one.

1110
01:03:10.700 --> 01:03:14.360
This 8p12 amplification, which spans FGFR1, defines

1111
01:03:14.400 --> 01:03:17.540
another nearly 6% of these tumors, and so forth.

1112
01:03:17.580 --> 01:03:19.220
And we've characterized these ad nauseam.

1113
01:03:19.260 --> 01:03:21.540
We've mapped their structural variant landscape.

1114
01:03:22.080 --> 01:03:24.710
They are wildly rearranged in a focal manner.

1115
01:03:25.980 --> 01:03:28.820
And so we know that copy number is playing a key role in driving their disease

1116
01:03:28.840 --> 01:03:32.620
progression. Now, we've also shown, intriguingly, that these

1117
01:03:32.660 --> 01:03:36.450
women that have HER2 positive disease, as well as those with estrogen receptor

1118
01:03:37.420 --> 01:03:41.370
positive disease that are high risk, shown here in this orange color, are heavily

1119
01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:43.100
immune depleted. Not exclusively.

1120
01:03:43.160 --> 01:03:46.620
You can see some are more fibrotic, some are immune and rich non-fibrotic, but

