01:04:08.260 --> 01:04:10.710
distinguish HER2 positive from ER positive high risk.

1128
01:04:10.820 --> 01:04:13.600
What distinguishes them is their focal copy number alterations and where those

1129
01:04:13.620 --> 01:04:16.140
reside. So these tumors are very similar.

1130
01:04:16.179 --> 01:04:19.440
And this led us to the question, well, these patients that have high-risk ER

1131
01:04:19.460 --> 01:04:22.220
positive disease are immune depleted, but what do we know about their

1132
01:04:22.300 --> 01:04:25.020
microenvironments beyond what we can infer from bulk data?

1133
01:04:26.300 --> 01:04:30.270
So this leads me to really an area I want to focus on, which is we know that

1134
01:04:30.300 --> 01:04:32.900
these women have very high risk. We know that their genome is determinant.

1135
01:04:32.940 --> 01:04:34.860
We can predict that risk for two decades.

1136
01:04:34.880 --> 01:04:37.920
But what might the microenvironment tell us about these patients as well?

1137
01:04:38.740 --> 01:04:42.240
So we embarked on a study. This is the first set of patients that we

1138
01:04:42.340 --> 01:04:46.260
profiled. We have roughly 336 women with ER

1139
01:04:46.320 --> 01:04:49.900
positive HER2 negative disease for whom we have 20 years of clinical follow-up.

1140
01:04:50.600 --> 01:04:54.170
We put them on a tissue microarray, and we use the CosMX,

1141
01:04:54.720 --> 01:04:58.530
used to be NanoString, now Bruker platform, to profile them at either 1,000 plex

1142
01:04:58.620 --> 01:05:01.970
or 6,000 plex, looking at that many transcripts.

1143
01:05:02.860 --> 01:05:04.380
With this, we can do a number of things.

1144
01:05:04.400 --> 01:05:07.920
We can define cell types, we can define cellular niches, we can look at cell-cell

1145
01:05:07.960 --> 01:05:11.320
interactions, and we can do all the kinds of things that I told you about with

1146
01:05:11.340 --> 01:05:14.960
protein, looking at diversity, densities, and ratios.

1147
01:05:15.400 --> 01:05:18.640
There are thousands of metrics we can compute from these spatial data.

1148
01:05:19.400 --> 01:05:22.580
But our goal was really to ask, can we create this kind of integrated tumor

1149
01:05:22.700 --> 01:05:23.320
ecosystem?

1150
01:05:24.800 --> 01:05:28.760
Now, this is just to reassure you that across these several hundred

