01:07:34.116 --> 01:07:34.836
integrative subtypes.

1189
01:07:35.636 --> 01:07:39.296
What we see now is that determination of the microenvironment

1190
01:07:39.416 --> 01:07:43.336
layers on top of what we had defined previously based on the genome alone,

1191
01:07:43.356 --> 01:07:46.836
and these patients that are ER-positive, typical risk, but niche zero

1192
01:07:46.856 --> 01:07:50.236
high have a pretty poor prognosis. We might have misclassified them.

1193
01:07:50.276 --> 01:07:51.936
We might have thought that they would do better.

1194
01:07:51.976 --> 01:07:55.156
They are not, in fact, typical risk. They're doing far worse.

1195
01:07:55.216 --> 01:07:58.636
So what this means, and we can show it in a multivariate Cox proportional hazard

1196
01:07:58.656 --> 01:08:02.536
analysis, is that in fact, layering on TMA information improves the

1197
01:08:02.576 --> 01:08:04.776
