01:08:26.596 --> 01:08:30.436
cells are all clustering. And this is really telling us that these

1205
01:08:30.496 --> 01:08:34.486
groups of cells are interacting more than we would expect by

1206
01:08:34.536 --> 01:08:34.906
chance.

1207
01:08:36.276 --> 01:08:39.816
And you can, in fact, see that the fibroblasts are behaving in a somewhat similar

1208
01:08:39.826 --> 01:08:43.316
fashion, and that this is associated with relapse risk.

1209
01:08:43.717 --> 01:08:47.436
So now we're observing an additional pattern of

1210
01:08:47.976 --> 01:08:51.936
co-localization. It turns out that this is all happening in niche

1211
01:08:52.096 --> 01:08:55.856
zero. So niche zero is not so boring after all, because in fact,

1212
01:08:56.416 --> 01:08:59.696
what we're really observing is that there's a dramatic enrichment of

1213
01:08:59.757 --> 01:09:03.706
perivascular-like cells co-localizing with fibroblasts, and that's happening

1214
01:09:03.776 --> 01:09:05.436
