01:21:58.112 --> 01:22:02.062
cells. At the same point, there are structural changes that we also observe

1441
01:22:02.132 --> 01:22:05.992
and a lot of crosstalk there. So one of the ways that we're trying

1442
01:22:06.052 --> 01:22:09.682
to parse that, and it's a simplistic route, but because we've also

1443
01:22:09.712 --> 01:22:13.642
established patient-derived organoid models of disease, and we heard about

1444
01:22:13.652 --> 01:22:17.592
the importance of 3D, we can go back in those models, imperfect though

1445
01:22:17.632 --> 01:22:20.422
they may be, and try to reconstitute some of those

1446
01:22:21.292 --> 01:22:24.552
two-way, maybe up to three-way interactions.

1447
01:22:25.192 --> 01:22:25.642
Mm-hmm.

1448
01:22:25.682 --> 01:22:29.062
And indeed, we're able to corroborate some of the predictions that are made from

1449
01:22:29.072 --> 01:22:32.402
the patient data. So our view is let's start with the patient data and go back and

1450
01:22:32.432 --> 01:22:33.321
try to perturb this.

1451
01:22:33.772 --> 01:22:33.872
Okay.

1452
01:22:35.272 --> 01:22:38.352
And I say this because, of course, everything we see in the tissue is correlative.

1453
01:22:38.372 --> 01:22:38.381
Yeah.

1454
01:22:38.392 --> 01:22:42.242
It's not causation, and the big challenge we have for a lot of

1455
01:22:42.272 --> 01:22:44.381
these is how do we then perturb that-

1456
01:22:44.412 --> 01:22:45.102
Interconvert to something better

1457
01:22:45.112 --> 01:22:46.032
... en masse. Right.

1458
01:22:46.062 --> 01:22:46.152
Yeah.

1459
01:22:46.202 --> 01:22:48.572
And there's other tools. There's organ-on-a-chip type models.

1460
01:22:48.622 --> 01:22:48.622
Yeah.

1461
01:22:48.632 --> 01:22:51.992
We could obviously go in vivo. Unfortunately, in vivo for ER positive disease is

1462
01:22:52.032 --> 01:22:53.192
not a great system either.

1463
01:22:53.352 --> 01:22:53.712
Yeah.

1464
01:22:54.612 --> 01:22:58.492
But there are things happening at that border that I think

1465
01:22:58.632 --> 01:23:01.452
really matter, and it isn't just the density of cancer cells.

1466
01:23:01.692 --> 01:23:01.992
Mm-hmm.

1467
01:23:02.012 --> 01:23:05.262
And what I didn't say here, but we have looked carefully at, and I think this is

1468
01:23:05.292 --> 01:23:09.012
